'''''GBA Championship Basketball: Two-on-Two''''' is a [[1986 in video gaming|1986]] [[computer game|computer]] [[basketball]] game for the [[IBM PC compatible|PC]], [[Amiga]], [[Apple II series|Apple II]], [[Apple IIGS]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Atari ST]], [[ZX Spectrum]] and [[Commodore 64]]. It was developed by [[Dynamix]] and [[video game publisher|published]] by [[Activision]].<ref>[http://hol.abime.net/2708 GBA Championship Basketball:Two-on-Two] at hol.abime.net</ref>

== Gameplay ==
From a camera located flying over the center of the court the game featured a two on two basketball game, allowing one or two players.<ref>[http://www.mobygames.com/game/dos/gba-championship-basketball-two-on-two's GBA Championship Basketball:Two-on-Two] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303235723/http://www.mobygames.com/game/dos/gba-championship-basketball-two-on-two's |date=March 3, 2016}} at mobygames.com</ref>

==Reception==
''GBA'' was Activision's second best-selling Commodore game as of late 1987.<ref name="ferrell198712">{{cite news | url=https://archive.org/stream/1987-12-computegazette/Compute_Gazette_Issue_54_1987_Dec#page/n17/mode/2up | title=The Commodore Games That Live On And On | work=Compute's Gazette | date=December 1987 | accessdate=24 January 2015 | author=Ferrell, Keith | pages=18–22}}</ref> ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' praised the Commodore 64 version of ''GBA'' for improving on ''[[One on One: Dr. J vs. Larry Bird]]'' by adding a full court, teammate, and league play.<ref name="teverbaugh198608">{{cite news | title=Sports Scoreboard | magazine=Computer Gaming World | date=August 1986 | url=http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1986&pub=2&id=30 | accessdate=1 November 2013 | author=Teverbaugh, Rick | pages=20}}</ref> The [[Apple IIGS]] version of the game was reviewed in 1988 in ''[[Dragon (magazine)|Dragon]]'' #129 by Hartley, Patricia, and Kirk Lesser in "The Role of Computers" column. The reviewers gave the game 4 out of 5 stars.<ref name="Dragon129">{{cite journal | title=The Role of Computers | last1=Lesser | last2=Lesser | last3=Lesser | first1=Hartley | first2=Patricia | first3=Kirk | journal=Dragon | issue=129 | date=January 1988 | pages=32–42}}</ref> ''[[Compute!]]'' called the Apple IIGS version "a delightful game whether you're playing or just watching", praising the graphics and sound.<ref name="trunzo198804">{{cite news | url=https://archive.org/stream/1988-04-compute-magazine/Compute_Issue_095_1988_Apr#page/n21/mode/2up | title=GBA Championship Basketball: Two-On-Two | work=Compute! | date=April 1988 | accessdate=10 November 2013 | author=Trunzo, James V. | pages=20}}</ref>

